cs.CV, cs.BI, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the estimation of cardiac muscle deformation using a point-wise approach, which involves image processing and numerical methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves biomedical applications, which suggests that it could belong to cs.BI (Bioinformatics). The use of numerical methods and boundary conditions to solve the governing equation in deformation suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the modeling of mechanical behavior, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
